TargetLocators:
Locators:
id,name,className, linktext, p linktext, xpath,CSS selector.

id - if there is any number in id, we shouldn't use that.
Class - if there is space in Class, we shouldn't use that. 

1.Absolute xpath - / we'll never use in reality.
2.Relative xpath - //
2.1.Basic=
2.2.Axes
Basics:
1.Attribute based.
//tagname[@attribute='value']
2.partial attribute based.
//tagname[contains(@attribute,'value']
3.text based.
//tagname[text()='value']
4.partial text based.
//tagname[contains(text(),'value']
5.collections.
(xpath)[index]


Axes:
we're going to build relationship between HTML tags.

1.Parent -> Child
//tagname[@attribute='value']/ child tagname or Child x-path.
//p[@class='top']/label

2.Child -> Parent
//p[@class='top']/parent::form

                                                                                                                                            following-sibling::   ancestor::  following-sibling::   preceding-sibling following::label
                                                                                                                                            Preceding-sibling::
ance
3.GrandParent -> GrandChild
//tagname[@attribute='value']//child tagname or Child x-path.
//form[@id='login']//label[@for='username']

4.GrandChild -> GrandParent
//label[text()='Username']/ancestor::form
//label[@for='username']/ancestor::form


5.Elder Sibling -> Younger Sibling
//tagname[@attribute='value']/following-sibling:: younger sibling tagname or x-path
//label[@for='username']/following-sibling::input


6.Younger Sibling  -> Elder Sibling
//input[@type='text']/preceding-sibling::label
//input[@id='username']/preceding-sibling::label


7.Elder Cousin -> Younger Cousin
//input[@class='inputLogin']/following::label
//input[@id='username']/following::label

8.Younger Cousin -> Elder Cousin
//label[@for='password']/preceding::input
//label[@for='password']/preceding::input




Target Locator:
Alert,frame and window:
Alert  is basically designed and developed from JS.
When the alert is populated, the entire is frozen
Alert Components:
1.Simple Alert - msg - ok
2.Confirm Alert - msg - yes/no
3.Promt Alert -msg - 
4.SweetAlert - can inspect this.

Exception:
NoAlertPresentException - no alert available but you've written code to candle alert
UnHandledAlertException - There will be an alert, but you missed to write code to candle it.

